<div id="pf42" class="pf w4 hd" data-page-no="42"><div class="pc pc42 w4 hd"><div class="t m371 xa hf ya2b ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3. </div><div class="t m6e2 xc hf y383 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The Levitical order had a line of priests but the new order has </div><div class="t m28 x44 hf ya2c ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m2d7 xc8 hf ya2c ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">only </div><div class="t m28 x34 hf ya2c ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m512 x27 hf y385 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">priest (verses 23, 24). </div><div class="t m373 xa hf ya2d ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">4. </div><div class="t m176 x52 hf ya2e ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Under the new order Christ continues </div><div class="t m28 x12 hf y387 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m1d9 xdb hf ya2f ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(verse 24). </div><div class="t m374 xa hf y389 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">5. </div><div class="t m1e9 x52 hf ya30 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Under this order Christ is able to </div><div class="t m28 x31 hf ya30 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m2b7 x7b hf y687 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(verse 25). </div><div class="t m6b4 xa hf ya31 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">6. </div><div class="t m647 x52 hf y9da ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">As priest of the new order Christ is </div><div class="t m28 x30 hf y38b ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m1d9 xdb hf ya32 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(verse 26). </div><div class="t m341 xa hf y7 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">7. </div><div class="t me7 x52 hf y7 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Christ has no need to offer </div><div class="t m28 xaf hf y7 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m1d9 xdb hf y689 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(verse 27). </div><div class="t m6c6 xa hf y38e ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">8. </div><div class="t m345 x52 hf ya33 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Mortals served as priests under the Levitical system but Christ is </div><div class="t m9b x52 hf y2d3 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">consecrated </div><div class="t m28 x15 hf y2d3 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t mda xdb hf ya34 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(verse 28). </div><div class="t m3e1 x43 hf ya35 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">FURTHER STUDY AND MEDITATION: </div><div class="t m4ad xa hf yc4 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Read </div><div class="t m1b8 x63 hf yc4 ff6 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Early Writings, </div><div class="t m6e3 x18 hf ya36 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">pages 250-256. </div><div class="t m6e4 xa hf ya37 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;The record tells us nothing about his [Melchizedek&apos;s] pedigree, his </div><div class="t m6e5 x43 hf y79 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">birth, or death. So far as the record goes, no beginning nor end of life is </div><div class="t m194 x5d hf y37c ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">given; and it was the custom, therefore, among the Jews, to speak of such </div><div class="t m3d1 x5d hf y37e ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">as having no genealogy, no mother, no father, no beginning of days, nor </div><div class="t m3d3 x5d hf ya38 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">end of life. And considering that all these expressions are used simply </div><div class="t m92 x5d hf ya39 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">from the standpoint of the record, there is no difficulty. Melchizedek sud-</div><div class="t m53a x43 hf ya3a ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">denly appears upon the scene of action, an eminent servant of God, com-</div><div class="t m609 x43 hf ya3b ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">bining, in his own person the double office of king and priest. All before </div><div class="t mff x43 hf ya3c ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">him is blank; all following him is blank. Neither birth nor death appearing </div><div class="t m558 x5d hf ya3d ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">in the scene, he becomes a fitting prototype of Christ in his position of </div><div class="t mb x43 hf ya3e ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">priest-king in this dispensation.&quot;—Uriah Smith, </div><div class="t m5b4 x7 hf ya3f ff6 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Review and Herald, </div><div class="t m68c x43 hf ya40 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Nov. 5, 1895. </div><div class="t m4b7 x5d hf y861 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">SUMMARY: The knowledge that we have a merciful, compassionate High </div><div class="t m1c1 x43 hf ya41 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Priest in heaven gives us strong confidence. He is the one and only true </div><div class="t m15c x43 hf ya42 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Priest; His priesthood is superior to every other priesthood, the Levitical </div><div class="t m55e x43 hf ya43 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">order included. We need no other mediator, no human priest. </div><div class="t m312 x61 hf y296 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">APPLICATION: </div><div class="t m192 x5d hf ya44 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">o </div><div class="t m12c x62 hf y9f3 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What difference does it make to me to know that I have &quot;such an high </div><div class="t m250 xa hf ya45 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">priest&quot;? Consider, for example, does it make a difference: when I feel </div><div class="t m3e7 xa hf ya46 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">discouraged? in my concept of heaven? in my hour of test? </div><div class="t m192 x5d hf y83e ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">o </div><div class="t m524 x62 hf ya47 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Sometimes we feel lonely and wonder if anyone cares. Do the ideas </div><div class="t m4eb xa hf ya48 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">presented in this lesson suggest where I can find help? </div><div class="t m192 x5d hf ya49 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">o </div><div class="t m41c x62 hf ya4a ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">How can I make the marvelous truths of this lesson real to others? </div><div class="t m688 x43 hf ya4b ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">NOTES: </div><div class="t m245 x61 ha y9fb ff1 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">62 </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
